Reasoning: The paper uses entropy statistics to develop an indicator of mutual information among demand, supply, and technological capabilities in the medical context. It also uses Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) of MEDLINE/PubMed to identify publications within the categories “Diseases” (C), “Drugs and Chemicals” (D), “Analytic, Diagnostic, and Therapeutic Techniques and Equipment” (E) as knowledge representations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for the use of entropy statistics, Digital Libraries (cs.DL) for the use of MeSH, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the triple helix model, Cybernetics (cs.CY) for the focus on reducing uncertainty, and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) for the use of statistical methods.
